msgctxt "sn36.19:3.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.10"
msgid "Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā, santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.19:3.11"
msgid "Neva sakkhi āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ saññāpetuṃ, na panāsakkhi pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ saññāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "But neither was able to persuade the other. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.19:3.12"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ. "
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Udāyī and Pañcakaṅga. "

# NOTE: abhivadevta is in the parallel passage at MN 59, obviously is elided here.
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn36.19:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "He went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "sn36.19:4.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.225, sc5
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.1"
msgid "“Santameva, ānanda, pariyāyaṃ pañcakaṅgo thapati udāyissa bhikkhuno nābbhanumodi; "
msgstr "“Ānanda, the explanation by the mendicant Udāyī, which the master builder Pañcakaṅga didn’t agree with, was quite correct. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.2"
msgid "santañca panānanda, pariyāyaṃ udāyī bhikkhu pañcakaṅgassa thapatino nābbhanumodi. "
msgstr "But the explanation by Pañcakaṅga, which Udāyī didn’t agree with, was also quite correct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.3"
msgid "Dvepi mayā, ānanda, vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr "In one explanation I’ve spoken of two feelings. In another explanation I’ve spoken of three feelings, or five, six, eighteen, thirty-six, or a hundred and eight feelings. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.4"
msgid "Tissopi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.5"
msgid "Pañcapi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.6"
msgid "Chapi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhārasāpi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.8"
msgid "Chattiṃsāpi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhasatampi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.10"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo. "
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways. "

#. VAR: viharissantīti → viharissanti (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.11"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ, na samanumaññissanti, na samanujānissanti, na samanumodissanti, tesaṃ etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharissantīti. "
msgstr "This being so, you can expect that those who don’t concede, approve, or agree with what has been well spoken will argue, quarrel, and fight, continually wounding each other with barbed words. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.12"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo. "
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.13"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ samanumaññissanti samanujānissanti samanumodissanti, tesaṃ etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharissantīti. "
msgstr "This being so, you can expect that those who do concede, approve, or agree with what has been well spoken will live in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn36.19:6.1"
msgid "Pañcime, ānanda, kāmaguṇā. "
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.3"
msgid "Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā … pe … "
msgstr "Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. … "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.4"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.5"
msgid "Ime kho, ānanda, pañca kāmaguṇā. "
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.6"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, ānanda, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—"
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is called sensual pleasure. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.7"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.8"
msgid "Ye kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "There are those who would say "

# NOTE: Following PTS reading sattā for santam, although I am not certain of this.
msgctxt "sn36.19:6.9"
msgid "‘etapparamaṃ santaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti—"
msgstr "that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings experience. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.10"
msgid "idaṃ nesāhaṃ nānujānāmi. "
msgstr "But I don’t acknowledge that. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.12"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.226, sc7
msgctxt "sn36.19:7.1"
msgid "Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca? "
msgstr "And what is that pleasure? "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.3"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.4"
msgid "Ye kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "There are those who would say "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.5"
msgid "‘etapparamaṃ santaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti—"
msgstr "that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings experience. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.6"
msgid "idaṃ nesāhaṃ nānujānāmi. "
msgstr "But I don’t acknowledge that. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.8"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn36.19:8.1"
msgid "Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca? "
msgstr "And what is that pleasure? "

msgctxt "sn36.19:8.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhu, vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "sn36.19:8.3"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that. "

